  "html": "<h1>Applies to</h1>\n  <ul>\n    <li>C&#43;&#43;</li>\n  </ul>\n  <h1>What to Check For</h1>\n  <p>Verify that error handling functions are centralized, for example in a separate class, or a set of classes.</p>\n  <h1>Why</h1>\n  <p>Centralized error handling is easier to test and implement correctly. Handling errors is important for security, so better error handling improves security.</p>\n  <h1>How to Check</h1>\n  <p>Look for code that handles errors. Verify that functions and classes are written specifically for handling errors, instead of handling errors in code that may cause them.</p>\n  <h1>How to Fix</h1>\n  <p>Write utility classes and functions for handling errors. Use these functions instead of handling errors in code that may cause them.</p>\n  <h1>Additional Resources</h1>\n  <ul>\n    <li>For more information about the benefits of centralizing error handling, please see <a href=\"https://www.securecoding.cert.org/confluence/display/cplusplus/ERR00-CPP.&#43;Adopt&#43;and&#43;implement&#43;a&#43;consistent&#43;and&#43;comprehensive&#43;error-handling&#43;policy\">https://www.securecoding.cert.org/confluence/display/cplusplus/ERR00-CPP.&#43;Adopt&#43;and&#43;implement&#43;a&#43;consistent&#43;and&#43;comprehensive&#43;error-handling&#43;policy</a></li>\n  </ul>\n  <h1>Related Items</h1>\n  <ul>\n    <li>\n      <a href=\"/article/e4a3052e-13f2-4062-9a83-49185ff14b0a\">Centralize Error Handling</a>\n    </li>\n  </ul>"
